article.headline: Weber State beats North Dakota 24-12
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Jadrian Clark had three touchdown passes and Weber State notched its first win of the season on Saturday, a 24-12 victory over North Dakota. Clark's third touchdown pass went 8 yards to Zach Smith, putting Weber State (1-9, 1-5 Big Sky) up 24-3 with 10:35 left in the third quarter. Clark finished 19 of 31 for 235 yards and Cameron Livingston had five catches for 116 yards. After Josh Kealamakia's 42-yard field goal in the first, Clark had two second-quarter touchdown passes to make it 17-0 with 3:49 left in the half. Reid Taubenheim kicked a 21-yarder just before halftime to get North Dakota(3-7, 1-5) on the board, and Keaton Studsrud's 23-yard touchdown pass to Tucker Nordby made it 24-10 late in third. Jer Garman had 24 carries for 137 yards for North Dakota.
